<s docid="AP900623-0009" num="57" wdcount="2"> A U.S.</s>
<s docid="AP900623-0009" num="58" wdcount="31"> Army band played ``That is the Berlin Atmosphere,'' a stirring old song about the old Berlin, as the white checkpoint building was lifted to within 30 feet of Mrs. Wobig's window.</s>
<s docid="AP900623-0009" num="59" wdcount="12"> A sign saying ``What a pity, Checkpoint Charlie,'' hung from her sill.</s>
<s docid="AP900623-0009" num="60" wdcount="11"> ``I saw Kennedy, Reagan and Carter give speeches here,'' she said.</s>
